    "body": "End-to-end support for resolving LDS partition conflicts in GFX1250 GEMMs and a few related compiler hardenings.\r\n\r\n- Gluon layout helper\r\nAdd make_partitioned_dot_layouts(...): builds PartitionedSharedLayouts for A/B together with a matching AMDWMMALayout so the resulting WMMA tiling avoids LDS partition conflicts. Supports 4- and 8-warp configurations and both transposed/non-transposed operands.\r\n- inferTransOpEncoding now handles PartitionedSharedEncodingAttr: recurses into the per-piece partition layout and remaps partitionDim through the inverse of the transpose order.\r\n- Add triton::DotOp, DotScaledOp, CallOp, ReturnOp, FuncOp to the vetted-ops list in isOpVettedForGenericEncoding.\r\nReject DotOp / DotScaledOp whose result encoding is not a permutation-matrix linear layout, except for AMD WMMA paths which are the only ones validated against generic layouts. Generic encodings now fail the pattern with a clear diagnostic instead of silently miscompiling.\r\n- Add end-to-end runtime GEMM tests that exercise RESOLVE_PARTITION_CONFLICTS=True across various block shapes, K-contiguous and N-contiguous B layouts, multiple NUM_BUFFERS, and fp16 problem sizes.\r\n- Extend gemm_async_pipelined_kernel to support K-contiguous B with both TDM and AsyncCopy.\r\n",
    "created_at": "2026-04-27T19:33:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-29T15:50:17Z",
